⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Squealer
node AFM · AFM · ⟦Squealer:AFM:8e4a83⟧

WHO   — Squealer — the propagandist
WHAT  — The voice of the regime: he explains every betrayal, revises every memory, and rewrites the commandments by night.
WHERE — AFM · ANIMAL FARM  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because tyranny runs on narrative — Squealer is the apparatus that makes the animals doubt what they saw with their own eyes.
HOW   — By smooth lies, statistics, and the steady, nocturnal editing of the words painted on the barn wall.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I can turn black into white before your eyes — and by morning the commandment will read differently, and you will not quite remember the old one.

